Enum NPCs

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<NPCs>
      src.enums.NPCs
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<NPCs>
public enum NPCs
extends java.lang.Enum<NPCs>

Class that keeps track of different NPC types. Each NPC has a type for the map format, and a string that they will say when the player talks to them.

Author:
Darren Watts date 11/15/07

setStats

public void setStats(java.lang.String name,
                     java.lang.String talk,
                     java.lang.String image,
                     java.lang.String soundFile)
Sets this NPCs name and text. The text is what will be sent to the messages window when a player talks to this NPC. This will be set when reading in from a scenario file.

Parameters:
name - String : name of the NPC.
talk - String : message of the NPC.
image - String : image location
soundFile - String : path to sound file
